@rjeberhard @ddsharpe what do you think?
i do not like the style of relying on an exception being thrown. if you think there may be one, i prefer to explicitly catch it and write an assertion about whether it was/was not thrown, its type, etc.
i think the real issue is that someone could independently change any of these methods, and maybe they no longer throw an exception, and now this test would be broken, but we would not know.

